# Pearls content pipeline (year-scoped)

Canonical operator guide: `WORK-FLOW.md`.

When the user asks to parse / prepare / enrich a year (e.g. «парсим 2019»):

1. Confirm VPN is on before any `metadata:ai` step.
2. `npm run content:year -- <year>`
3. Review structure in `data/parsed/<year>/`
4. Always run `npm run metadata:ai -- --year=<year> --write` for new year data
5. `npm run generate:downloads -- --year=<year>`
6. Commit `data/parsed`, then ship downloads + code

## Titles = AI only

- Final `documentTitle` comes from the OpenAI metadata step, not from local regex/font heuristics.
- Parser heuristics prepare structure (splits, header/body/footer). They are not the authority for titles.
- If OpenAI returns `403 Country, region, or territory not supported` (or CLI prints `ВКЛЮЧИ ВПН!!! МОДЕЛЬ НЕДОСТУПНА!`), stop immediately. Do not invent titles locally. Tell the user to enable VPN and rerun `metadata:ai`.

## Other rules

- Always pass `--year` or `--file`. Never run prepare/parse/AI against the whole archive by default.
- Do not put `SOURCE_PERALS` on production.
- Do not hand-edit `data/parsed/` JSON.
- AI context sources: brochure header/body preview, `SOURCE_PERALS/source-map.json`, `data/lecture-data-export.json`, and already-reviewed years only (never unprocessed future years as “examples”).
